entry.def: If something juts out, it sticks out above or beyond a surface.

example.ex: The northern end of the island juts out like a long, thin finger into the sea...
example.tran: 岛屿的北端像一根细长的手指一样伸入海中。

example.ex: Tombstones jutted out of the ground in broken clusters...
example.tran: 墓碑三三两两地竖立在地面上。

entry.tran: （使）（使身体部位）凸出；（尤指）翘起（下巴）
entry.def: If you jut a part of your body, especially your chin, or if it juts, you push it forward in an aggressive or determined way.

example.ex: His jaw jutted stubbornly forward; he would not be denied...
example.tran: 他的下巴倔强地翘着；他不会甘心被拒绝。

example.ex: Gwen jutted her chin forward and did not answer the teacher...
example.tran: 格温下巴翘得高高的，没有回答老师的问题。
